  "notes": "Primary source RFEG (rfegolf.es club id=348): per-hole par, hcp and meters for Blancas/Amarillas/Azules/Rojas plus ratings. Distances and pars cross-check exactly with golfingholiday.com and 18birdies scorecards (both platforms mislabel the meter figures as yards). All per-hole sums match published totals exactly. Discrepancy: stroke-index allocation differs between RFEG (used here: SI front 15,13,7,9,11,5,1,3,17; back 8,4,18,12,2,14,10,16,6) and the 18birdies/golfingholiday card (front 17,5,13,9,15,3,1,7,11; back 4,10,14,12,2,18,6,16,8); both agree hole 7 is SI 1 and hole 14 SI 2. RFEG, as the official federation source, was followed. RFEG applies the same hcp allocation to all tees. Blancas and Amarillas are rated for men only; Azules and Rojas are rated for both genders (women's entries emitted with same distances). RFEG also lists a separate 9-hole P&P 'Verdes' pitch-and-putt recorrido (par 27, 942 m, CR 52.4/61 men, 53.9/72 women) which is excluded as it is not part of the 18-hole championship card. Blancas CR published as 73 (assumed 73.0) and Rojas women 74 (assumed 74.0)."
